            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Restore NASA Science to $9 billion to ensure U.S. leadership and workforce stability following FY 2026 budgetary disruptions.\n* Local PA-2 impact through support for Temple University ($334,239 in cumulative grants) and technical publishing via Iop Publishing Incorporated ($68,250 contract).\n* High-yield 3:1 economic return on federal investment, driving demand for Pennsylvania's high-tech workforce and national STEM talent pipeline.\n* Execution of National Academies' Decadal Survey priorities to maintain the American competitive advantage in space exploration over international rivals like China.",
